{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_017z51e1oHciBdaQ81nSMP1k","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a comprehensive summary of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. MachineConfig YAML Examples with base64 / Inline Content\n\n### Chrony configuration via base64 (the canonical example)\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-workers-chrony-configuration.yaml`**\n\nThis is the primary chrony+base64 example. The key field:\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  files:\n  - contents:\n      source: data:text/plain;charset=utf-8;base64,cG9vbCAwLnJoZWwucG9vbC5udHAub3JnIGlidXJzdApkcmlmdGZpbGUgL3Zhci9saWIvY2hyb255L2RyaWZ0Cm1ha2VzdGVwIDEuMCAzCnJ0Y3N5bmMKbG9nZGlyIC92YXIvbG9nL2Nocm9ueQo=\n    mode: 420\n    overwrite: true\n    path: /etc/chrony.conf\n```\nThe base64 string decodes to a standard chrony pool/drift/makestep config for `/etc/chrony.conf`.\n\n### GPG public key via base64\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/add-gpg-pub-key.yaml`**\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  files:\n  - contents:\n      source: data:;base64,<long-base64-blob>\n    path: /etc/machine-config-daemon/no-reboot/containers-gpg.pub\n```\n\n### Policy JSON via base64\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-policy-json.yaml`**\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  files:\n  - contents:\n      source: data:;base64,eyJkZWZhdWx0IjogW3sidHlwZSI6ICJpbnNlY3VyZUFjY2VwdEFueXRoaW5nIn1dfQo=\n    path: /etc/containers/policy.json\n```\n\n### Journald config with parameterized base64\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-worker-jrnl-configuration.yaml`**\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  files:\n    - contents:\n        source: data:text/plain;charset=utf-8;base64,${CONFIGURATION}\n        verification: {}\n      filesystem: root\n      mode: 420\n      path: /etc/systemd/journald.conf\n```\n\n### Inline data URI (non-base64)\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/server/testdata/machine-configs/test-config.yaml`**\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  files:\n    - contents:\n        source: \"data:,GROUP%3Dstable%0ASERVER%3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A32003%2Fv1%2Fupdate%0A\"\n      filesystem: root\n      mode: 420\n      path: /etc/coreos/update.conf\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Chrony / NTP Related MachineConfig Examples\n\n### File-based chrony config (base64)\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-workers-chrony-configuration.yaml`**\nWrites `/etc/chrony.conf` with a new pool NTP config.\n\n### Disabling chronyd service via systemd unit override\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/disable-chrony.yaml`**\n```yaml\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.2.0\n    systemd:\n      units:\n        - contents: |\n            [Unit]\n            Description=NTP client/server\n            ...\n            [Service]\n            ExecStart=/usr/sbin/chronyd $OPTIONS\n            ...\n          enabled: false\n          name: \"chronyd.service\"\n```\nThis shows both how to supply a full unit file and disable it.\n\n### chrony-wait.service dropin (internal template)\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/templates/common/_base/units/chrony-wait.service.yaml`**\nThis is a MCO-internal template (not a user-facing MachineConfig), but shows the dropin pattern:\n```yaml\nname: chrony-wait.service\ndropins:\n  - name: 10-skip-on-first-join.conf\n    contents: |\n      [Unit]\n      ConditionPathExists=/var/lib/kubelet/pki/kubelet-client-current.pem\n```\n\n### chronyd dropin via test (programmatic, not YAML)\nIn `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/mco_configdrift.go` (line 142), a test creates a dropin file for `chronyd.service` at `/etc/systemd/system/chronyd.service.d/10-chrony-drop-test.conf` with content `[Service]\\nEnvironment=\"FAKE_OPTS=fake-value\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Documented Patterns for Creating MachineConfig Resources\n\n### Official documentation\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md`**\n\nCanonical patterns from the docs:\n\n**File with data URI (Ignition v3.2.0, for OCP >= 4.7):**\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: worker-2864988432\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.2.0\n    storage:\n      files:\n      - contents:\n          source: data:,%20\n        mode: 384\n        path: /root/myfile\n```\n\n**kernelArguments example:**\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: \"master\"\n  name: 99-master-kargs-loglevel\nspec:\n  kernelArguments:\n    - 'loglevel=7'\n```\n\n**extensions example:**\n```yaml\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.2.0\n  extensions:\n    - usbguard\n```\n\n**kernelType example:**\n```yaml\nspec:\n  kernelType: realtime\n```\n\n### Generic test template (most flexible pattern)\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/generic-machine-config-template.yml`**\n\nThis template exposes all top-level spec fields as parameters and is the canonical \"generic\" pattern used throughout the test suite:\n```yaml\nspec:\n  kernelArguments: ${{KERNEL_ARGS}}\n  osImageURL: ${OS_IMAGE}\n  extensions: ${{EXTENSIONS}}\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: ${IGNITION_VERSION}   # defaults to 3.5.0\n    storage:\n      files: ${{FILES}}\n    systemd:\n      units: ${{UNITS}}\n    passwd:\n      users: ${{PWDUSERS}}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. MachineConfig API Types\n\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types.go`** (lines 305–360)\n\n```go\ntype MachineConfig struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec MachineConfigSpec `json:\"spec\"`  // optional\n}\n\ntype MachineConfigSpec struct {\n    OSImageURL                     string               `json:\"osImageURL\"`\n    BaseOSExtensionsContainerImage string               `json:\"baseOSExtensionsContainerImage\"`\n    Config                         runtime.RawExtension `json:\"config,omitempty\"`     // Ignition config object\n    KernelArguments                []string             `json:\"kernelArguments\"`\n    Extensions                     []string             `json:\"extensions\"`\n    FIPS                           bool                 `json:\"fips\"`\n    KernelType                     string               `json:\"kernelType\"`\n}\n```\n\nKey constants from the same file:\n- `MachineConfigRoleLabelKey = \"machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role\"` — the label that assigns a MachineConfig to a pool (e.g. `master`, `worker`)\n\n**Required fields summary:**\n- `apiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1`\n- `kind: MachineConfig`\n- `metadata.name` (required by Kubernetes)\n- `metadata.labels[\"machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role\"]` — required to target a pool\n- `spec.config.ignition.version` — current preferred value is `3.2.0` (or `3.5.0` in newer tests); `3.4.0` used for Ignition v3 kernel argument syntax\n- All `spec` fields are technically optional per the API, but `spec.config` with `ignition.version` is universally included\n\n**The `spec.config` field** is a raw embedded Ignition config object. For files, the `storage.files[].contents.source` field takes a data URI, either:\n- Plain URL-encoded: `data:,<url-encoded-content>`\n- Base64: `data:text/plain;charset=utf-8;base64,<base64>` or `data:;base64,<base64>`\n\n**`mode`** is decimal (e.g., `420` = octal `0644`, `384` = octal `0600`, `256` = octal `0400`)."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"131fbf26-a5b5-4c2d-a7f1-137a424d6e2a","uuid":"27af20da-1a51-4e35-ab90-564c8bdc817b","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:37:48.923Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"In the repository at /home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator, find:\n1. Example MachineConfig YAML files (especially any that configure files via base64 or inline content)\n2. Any existing chrony or NTP related MachineConfig examples\n3. The documented patterns for creating MachineConfig resources (look in docs/, examples/, or test fixtures)\n4. The MachineConfig API types to understand required fields (apiVersion, kind, spec.config structure)\n\nSearch breadth: medium. Return actual file paths and relevant content snippets.","agentId":"a72410ff514c682f1","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a comprehensive summary of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. MachineConfig YAML Examples with base64 / Inline Content\n\n### Chrony configuration via base64 (the canonical example)\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-workers-chrony-configuration.yaml`**\n\nThis is the primary chrony+base64 example. The key field:\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  files:\n  - contents:\n      source: data:text/plain;charset=utf-8;base64,cG9vbCAwLnJoZWwucG9vbC5udHAub3JnIGlidXJzdApkcmlmdGZpbGUgL3Zhci9saWIvY2hyb255L2RyaWZ0Cm1ha2VzdGVwIDEuMCAzCnJ0Y3N5bmMKbG9nZGlyIC92YXIvbG9nL2Nocm9ueQo=\n    mode: 420\n    overwrite: true\n    path: /etc/chrony.conf\n```\nThe base64 string decodes to a standard chrony pool/drift/makestep config for `/etc/chrony.conf`.\n\n### GPG public key via base64\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/add-gpg-pub-key.yaml`**\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  files:\n  - contents:\n      source: data:;base64,<long-base64-blob>\n    path: /etc/machine-config-daemon/no-reboot/containers-gpg.pub\n```\n\n### Policy JSON via base64\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-policy-json.yaml`**\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  files:\n  - contents:\n      source: data:;base64,eyJkZWZhdWx0IjogW3sidHlwZSI6ICJpbnNlY3VyZUFjY2VwdEFueXRoaW5nIn1dfQo=\n    path: /etc/containers/policy.json\n```\n\n### Journald config with parameterized base64\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-worker-jrnl-configuration.yaml`**\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  files:\n    - contents:\n        source: data:text/plain;charset=utf-8;base64,${CONFIGURATION}\n        verification: {}\n      filesystem: root\n      mode: 420\n      path: /etc/systemd/journald.conf\n```\n\n### Inline data URI (non-base64)\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/server/testdata/machine-configs/test-config.yaml`**\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  files:\n    - contents:\n        source: \"data:,GROUP%3Dstable%0ASERVER%3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A32003%2Fv1%2Fupdate%0A\"\n      filesystem: root\n      mode: 420\n      path: /etc/coreos/update.conf\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Chrony / NTP Related MachineConfig Examples\n\n### File-based chrony config (base64)\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/change-workers-chrony-configuration.yaml`**\nWrites `/etc/chrony.conf` with a new pool NTP config.\n\n### Disabling chronyd service via systemd unit override\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/disable-chrony.yaml`**\n```yaml\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.2.0\n    systemd:\n      units:\n        - contents: |\n            [Unit]\n            Description=NTP client/server\n            ...\n            [Service]\n            ExecStart=/usr/sbin/chronyd $OPTIONS\n            ...\n          enabled: false\n          name: \"chronyd.service\"\n```\nThis shows both how to supply a full unit file and disable it.\n\n### chrony-wait.service dropin (internal template)\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/templates/common/_base/units/chrony-wait.service.yaml`**\nThis is a MCO-internal template (not a user-facing MachineConfig), but shows the dropin pattern:\n```yaml\nname: chrony-wait.service\ndropins:\n  - name: 10-skip-on-first-join.conf\n    contents: |\n      [Unit]\n      ConditionPathExists=/var/lib/kubelet/pki/kubelet-client-current.pem\n```\n\n### chronyd dropin via test (programmatic, not YAML)\nIn `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/mco_configdrift.go` (line 142), a test creates a dropin file for `chronyd.service` at `/etc/systemd/system/chronyd.service.d/10-chrony-drop-test.conf` with content `[Service]\\nEnvironment=\"FAKE_OPTS=fake-value\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Documented Patterns for Creating MachineConfig Resources\n\n### Official documentation\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/MachineConfig.md`**\n\nCanonical patterns from the docs:\n\n**File with data URI (Ignition v3.2.0, for OCP >= 4.7):**\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: worker-2864988432\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.2.0\n    storage:\n      files:\n      - contents:\n          source: data:,%20\n        mode: 384\n        path: /root/myfile\n```\n\n**kernelArguments example:**\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfig\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: \"master\"\n  name: 99-master-kargs-loglevel\nspec:\n  kernelArguments:\n    - 'loglevel=7'\n```\n\n**extensions example:**\n```yaml\nspec:\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: 3.2.0\n  extensions:\n    - usbguard\n```\n\n**kernelType example:**\n```yaml\nspec:\n  kernelType: realtime\n```\n\n### Generic test template (most flexible pattern)\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/generic-machine-config-template.yml`**\n\nThis template exposes all top-level spec fields as parameters and is the canonical \"generic\" pattern used throughout the test suite:\n```yaml\nspec:\n  kernelArguments: ${{KERNEL_ARGS}}\n  osImageURL: ${OS_IMAGE}\n  extensions: ${{EXTENSIONS}}\n  config:\n    ignition:\n      version: ${IGNITION_VERSION}   # defaults to 3.5.0\n    storage:\n      files: ${{FILES}}\n    systemd:\n      units: ${{UNITS}}\n    passwd:\n      users: ${{PWDUSERS}}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. MachineConfig API Types\n\n**`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types.go`** (lines 305–360)\n\n```go\ntype MachineConfig struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec MachineConfigSpec `json:\"spec\"`  // optional\n}\n\ntype MachineConfigSpec struct {\n    OSImageURL                     string               `json:\"osImageURL\"`\n    BaseOSExtensionsContainerImage string               `json:\"baseOSExtensionsContainerImage\"`\n    Config                         runtime.RawExtension `json:\"config,omitempty\"`     // Ignition config object\n    KernelArguments                []string             `json:\"kernelArguments\"`\n    Extensions                     []string             `json:\"extensions\"`\n    FIPS                           bool                 `json:\"fips\"`\n    KernelType                     string               `json:\"kernelType\"`\n}\n```\n\nKey constants from the same file:\n- `MachineConfigRoleLabelKey = \"machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role\"` — the label that assigns a MachineConfig to a pool (e.g. `master`, `worker`)\n\n**Required fields summary:**\n- `apiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1`\n- `kind: MachineConfig`\n- `metadata.name` (required by Kubernetes)\n- `metadata.labels[\"machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role\"]` — required to target a pool\n- `spec.config.ignition.version` — current preferred value is `3.2.0` (or `3.5.0` in newer tests); `3.4.0` used for Ignition v3 kernel argument syntax\n- All `spec` fields are technically optional per the API, but `spec.config` with `ignition.version` is universally included\n\n**The `spec.config` field** is a raw embedded Ignition config object. For files, the `storage.files[].contents.source` field takes a data URI, either:\n- Plain URL-encoded: `data:,<url-encoded-content>`\n- Base64: `data:text/plain;charset=utf-8;base64,<base64>` or `data:;base64,<base64>`\n\n**`mode`** is decimal (e.g., `420` = octal `0644`, `384` = octal `0600`, `256` = octal `0400`)."}],"resolvedModel":"claude-sonnet-4-6","totalDurationMs":142660,"totalTokens":53928,"totalToolUseCount":47,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":790,"cache_read_input_tokens":50509,"output_tokens":2628,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":790},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"toolStats":{"readCount":19,"searchCount":0,"bashCount":28,"editFileCount":0,"linesAdded":0,"linesRemoved":0,"otherToolCount":0}}}
